
[1m[35mnlnav — The Logfile Navigator (custom fork)[0m

A fork of ]8;;https://lnav.org\[4mlnav[0m]8;;\¹ with added features for log analysis and security
investigation.

 [34m▌[0m[1] - https://lnav.org 

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

[1mAdded Features[0m

[4mTimestamp Normalization[0m

Normalize all displayed log timestamps to UTC
[37m[40m YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS[.sss] [0m format, regardless of the original
timezone or format in the file.

 Interface  How to use                                        
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 Key        Press [37m[40m y [0m to toggle on/off                        
 Command    [37m[40m :normalize-timestamps [on\|off] [0m                 
[1m SQL        [0m[1m[37m[40m SELECT normalize_ts('2024-03-25T10:30:00-05:00') [0m
[1m            → [0m[1m[37m[40m 2024-03-25 15:30:00 [0m[1m                           [0m

Useful when comparing logs from machines in different timezones or
with mixed timestamp formats (e.g. syslog + ISO 8601 in the same
file).

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

[4mSSH Traffic Flow Map[0m

Press [37m[40m 0 [0m to open an SSH statistics panel built from the currently
loaded log files.

 Interface  How to use                    
══════════════════════════════════════════
 Key        Press [37m[40m 0 [0m to toggle the panel 
 Command    [37m[40m :ssh-stats [0m                  

The panel shows three sections:

 [33m1.[0m [1mSSH Traffic Flow Map[0m — per-source-IP flow table with
    destination, outcome, authenticated user(s), and auth
    method (e.g. [37m[40m public key [0m, [37m[40m SSSD (LDAP/AD) [0m,
    [37m[40m Kerberos/GSSAPI [0m, [37m[40m MFA/Duo [0m, etc.)
 [33m2.[0m [1mSSH Event Summary[0m — counts of accepted, failed,
    invalid-user, disconnected, and other event types
 [33m3.[0m [1mIP Address Frequency[0m — all IPs extracted from logs,
    split into [1mPublic[0m and [1mPrivate[0m sub-groups

Supports both BSD syslog ([37m[40m Mar 25 HH:MM:SS host sshd[0m[34m[40m[[0m[37m[40mpid[0m[34m[40m]:[0m[37m[40m ... [0m) and
ISO syslog ([37m[40m 2026-03-25T13:03:20+00:00 host sshd[0m[34m[40m[[0m[37m[40mpid[0m[34m[40m]:[0m[37m[40m ... [0m) formats.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

[4mIOC Highlighting ([0m[4m[37m[40m --ioc [0m[4m)[0m

Flag known malicious IPs from a threat-intel file and have them
highlighted in both the log view and SSH stats panel.

 ▌[33m[40m$ [0m[37m[40mlnav --ioc /path/to/ioc.txt /var/log/auth.log    [0m

The IOC file is plain text — one or more IPv4 addresses per line, [37m[40m # [0m
comments supported. Matching IPs are highlighted with a dark
background ([37m[40m #2e3440 [0m) in the log view and in the SSH
flow/IP-frequency tables.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

[1mWhat lnav Does[0m

Given a set of files or directories, [1mlnav[0m will:

 [33m•[0m decompress as needed;
 [33m•[0m detect their format;
 [33m•[0m merge the files by time into a single view;
 [33m•[0m tail the files, follow renames, find new files in
   directories;
 [33m•[0m build an index of errors and warnings;
 [33m•[0m pretty-print JSON-lines.

Then, in the TUI, you can:

 [33m•[0m jump quickly to the previous/next error (press [37m[40m e [0m/[37m[40m E [0m);
 [33m•[0m search using regular expressions (press [37m[40m / [0m);
 [33m•[0m highlight text with a regular expression ([37m[40m :highlight [0m
   command);
 [33m•[0m filter messages using regular expressions or SQLite
   expressions;
 [33m•[0m pretty-print structured text (press [37m[40m P [0m);
 [33m•[0m view a histogram of messages over time (press [37m[40m i [0m);
 [33m•[0m analyze messages using SQLite (press [37m[40m ; [0m).

